# AutoDocJson Build and Deploy

## Commands /publish and /deploy

When the user requests **`/publish`** or **`/deploy`** (or "publish", "deploy", "build and deploy"):

Run from this project root:

```powershell
.\Build-And-Publish.ps1
```

This publishes the AutoDocJson.Web project to the staging share on `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\DedgeWinApps\AutoDocJson`. The IIS app pool picks up the new files automatically.

## Rules

- Do **not** run `Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1` or any other repo's publish script unless the user explicitly asks.
- Do **not** run `IIS-DeployApp.ps1` or `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` unless the user explicitly asks for IIS redeploy.
- Do **not** run `git add/commit/push` unless the user explicitly asks (use `/commit` for that).
- Do **not** manually stop `dotnet` or `AutoDocJson.Web` processes before publishing — the script handles this automatically.
